Williams et al. (2023) used FlyBase to identify orthologous genes in six species of Drosophila (D. melanogaster, D. ananassae, D. erecta, D. sechellia, D. simulans, and D. yakuba); however, this information is no longer available on FlyBase. Therefore, we used the NCBI database to find orthologs. To this end, we first used Ensembl Metazoa (release 62) to obtain NCBI gene IDs corresponding to FlyBase IDs. 

One of the two R files here identifies NCBI genes for those used in Williams et al. (2023) (Three_classes_from_Williams.R) and the other identifies the random genes in this study (Random_genes.R).